## Plan Summary

**Root cause:** Off-by-one error in `src/utils.ts`, line 7.

```typescript
// Current (buggy)
for (let i = 0; i < items.length - 1; i++) {

// Fixed
for (let i = 0; i < items.length; i++) {
```

The condition `i < items.length - 1` stops the loop one index too early — it exits before reaching the last element. Removing `- 1` fixes it.

**Impact:** 4 out of 6 tests are currently failing (all `processItems` tests except the empty-array case). The `sum` tests are unaffected.

**Change required:** One file, one line, removing ` - 1` from the loop condition. No test changes needed — the tests already assert the correct behavior.

